obo:UBERON_0001890  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1016  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The adhesive interactions of the synaptic adhesion molecule SynCAM 1 were mapped in this study.\nThe homophilic binding of SynCAM 1 extracellular domains in trans is shown in Fig. 5, using a bead aggregation assay and a cell-cell contact analysis.\nTesting heterophilic interactions, the affinity chromatography results in Fig. 6A show that heterologously expressed SynCAM 1 retains not only SynCAM 1 but also SynCAM 2 from adult rat forebrain extracts. Beads coated with SynCAMs 2 and 3 each retain SynCAM 1 from forebrain extracts. Heterophilic interactions of SynCAM 1 and SynCAM 2 are further supported by the analysis of cell-cell contact assembly in Fig. 6B. All interactions are Ca2+ independent.. Experimental description: \"Sequences encoding full-length SynCAM 2 (splice product 2) (Biederer, 2006), SynCAM 3 (splice product 2), and SynCAM 4 were amplified from a mousebrain cDNA library prepared at 9-11 weeks of age (Clontech #639400).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2017-09-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1016" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
